The area

Address
Neighborhood: Centrum
Amsterdams buzzing hub, with its sprawling network of tram rails and a seemingly constant flow of tourists and commuters, yields convenient access to some of the best sightseeing, shopping, and street life in Europe. Closest at hand are the Royal Palace, the quaint shops of Haalremmerdijk, the pedestrianized zones Kalverstraat and Dam Square with popular neighborhoods such as the Red Light District, and the Canal Ring hardly more than a moments stroll away. With the well-connected Centraal Station as Centrums base, it's easy to travel farther afield via one of the citys iconic trams.

    Cute but overpriced
    Definitely one for cat lovers! This museum is full of cat paintings, statues and many other forms of cat memorabilia. There are also a few live feline friends running around who are absolutely adorable. The staff are friendly and polite. Unfortunately the experience is overpriced at 10 per person. We were in and out within about 25 minutes. Compared with some of the other museums, this doesn't represent great value for money. All bags are removed from you at the door and there are no lockers, they are simply looked after by the staff.
    Visited November 2023
    Traveled as a couple
    Written November 23, 2023

  • TheAviator0765
    Ripon, United Kingdom1,032 contributions
    If You Love Cats, This is For You
    Quirky, off-beat, run by cat lovers. If you love cats, you'll love this place. If you don't, you'll feel you have wasted your 10 euros entrance fee. If it's for you, this is a good place to spend an hour. Located in an old mansion house, on several floors and with a back garden (open in early March), Katten Kabinet is a labour of love for all things cat. Lots of pictures, many featured cat themed advertisements going back to the late nineteenth century. Cat themed furniture, cat themed antiques, cat themed ornaments, cat themed items to buy (many being posters or cards of the advertisements), you get the gist. It's also home to a couple of cats; if you're lucky you may see one (totally ignoring all things human, it's nothing personal). Well, we liked it.
    Visited March 2024
    Traveled with family
    Written March 23, 2024

Great artwork, no cats
Nov 2024 Couples
I have a love for cats so knew I wanted to try this place out. Entry is a fair price and there is basically a house and garden to explore and see lots of different cat artworks, status and pictures. This was all very interesting and I especially enjoyed seeing the mummified cat which is something Ive never seen before.

However, based on reviews and the many litter trays dotted about the house, there were no cats. We went about an hour before closing time and it seemed the cats had had their fill for the day and had gone to bed. Not the worst thing in the world, but it wouldve been nice to see them.

Overall, I think if youre a cat lover, youll enjoy this. Otherwise, I think itll be a bit underwhelming.
Written November 14, 2024

Cat Lovers Paradise!
Oct 2024 Couples
KattenKabinet is a cat lovers paradise, consisting of several rooms of eclectic cat art, including a shrine where you can leave a message to your own cat. When we visited, there were also a few actual cats roaming around! This is definitely a quick visit, but a fun stop in. Bonus - you get a little peek into a beautiful canal house! I think some people might think this is overpriced, but I really enjoyed my brief stop here.

A Cozy Visit to the Cat Museum
Sep 2024 Solo
You can enjoy antiques and posters related to cats. While the exhibition isn't very large, it's understandable given the small rooms. There are also posters in the backyard, where you can take a refreshing break while viewing them. Some reviews mention 'not seeing any cats,' but it's important to remember that the cats aren't employees. Those who are observant might spot a cat hiding in the backyard. If you're lucky, you may even get to pet one dozing peacefully on the floor.
Written September 8, 2024
